Sr. what here above is coppy of my letter sent you, &itt seems itt gave not the
desired content, so have onely to add that up on examination of the notoriall att out
of the books of yd mele of the £17:12:5 that itt be made wright: & ext moted
by a sworne no tsary & so remaine
a 26 Juy 1681
London pickering & Robinson
Sr. in answer to yd of 11 curitt I have opened the pack of bayes most part of which is
sold. as also the kersies boath which prove indifferente well and will rendre accordingly
the lowest prised northrens are also well bought, butt not att all drest & press
to my minde, much less the finer sort, whoever shall endeavour to putt off all
before winter: I may assure you that I am served much better in all respects
in the northren cloathes from other handes which makes the proffitt exeeed
by 5 a 6 p. and good & well conditioned goods sell alwayes first & lest
whoever I hope you will finde yd acctt. towards which you may be confident
that no endeavour shall be wanting on my side I observe what you write
concerning tykes I do not know what acctt those finde that bestow 5 & 6 Pet.
more then I do besides now yara or thread from silesia(of which tijkes are
made is risen 20 Bct. as easely you may be informed off in london in
somuch that now I must pay for the least 10 stivers a peece more then
formelj you complaine of the 3 seales as true that as I write thi
I have payd for 6 peeces last markette day ƒ28: a peece & less I can not deliver
them now: so if you please not to have the 4p. returne them reely for
I shall make more of them here & though I have bought above 100 p yett
know verij well to putt y off att higher rates whoever to serve you, in case
you please I shall sende you the 65 p. you desired in a ½nights time viz
30 p. great lead att ƒ13:16 st fros aboard att Brugges

Amst De SAcbter van Homright
messr. 24 deser was aen ul mijnen leeften waer uen referre, sedert den ul van
selve dato bekomen waer door ul versoecht van monsr. Judocue de larabert
tot Brugge gein formeert te sijn de vrint is y seer bekent, ende kan
den selve ul seer wel recommandeeren sijnde een persoon al hoe wel souct
die te betrouwen is, ende die sijn affaires verstaet, soo dat ul naer mijn oordeel
niet qualijk kan doe hem te imployeeren doch alsoo mee rexpedicat ie va
den Heer Coots has beoaden, soo hadde den selve ul voor gestelt ul kan niet mieden
hem to imployteren, ende daer dobbel op gerust sijn het mij in different sijn
die ul wie u van begde ul aenspant, alsoo war soo veel ckweten sij trouwe
luyden sijn ingesloten remittere ul. 128: a 125½ in banco £66:18:8
op Ad. Dutquesnoy valt sanght waer voor ul de weerde gelieft int groordderen
endemijne rekeninge creditt te geven tgeene over is sal sich selve vinden
terwijlen nae cordiele groet
